bestiary.blocks.empty=No Notable Specimens Found
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.harleskinn_block.desc=A dense parasitic mineral grown from corrupted terrain.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.locs_block.desc=A calcified mass of tissue used as a structural anchor.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.fog_nullifier.desc=Destroys connected Fog Blocks. Breaks after the third use. Cannot be picked up.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.dispatchern.desc=§cIt hurts.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.assimilated_reed.desc=The rods are full of a jelly-like substance.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.infested_furnace.desc=Used to Smelt Parasite-specific Blocks and Items.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.biomass_block.desc=Hurts anything that touches it. It constantly seeps green vapors and dripping biomass. Parasites aren't harmed by it.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.residue_block.desc=Used in building recipes. Residue Bloomings naturally grow on this block.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.sick_alveoli.desc=A weakened, infected form of the Alveoli Block. It poisons any creature that touches it and will remain diseased until brought close to a Bronchial Tube.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.alveoli.desc=A primary source of airborne nutrients for underground mega-organs. Using a bottle on it gathers Alveolar Fluid, an important ingredient in biological brewing. It becomes sick if left too far from a Bronchial Tube.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.hair_follicle_block.desc=Transports airborne nutrients for underground mega-organs.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.parasite_barrier.desc=Pushes all SPParasites entities outwards. Can be cycled through a 1 - 10 chunk radius.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.assimilated_pumpkin.desc=Can be worn. Applies COTH.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.esca_bulb.desc=Smells and Feels like Rotting fish. Packed with Bioluminescence.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.node_redstone_lamp.desc=A fragile glass node wired into Dispatchers within a 250-block range. It lights up and outputs a comparator signal based on how close one is, and right-clicking it shows the nearest Dispatcher's tier and distance. Strength = Dispatcher Level §l|§r §oDistance = Dispatcher Distance ( 1 being the closest. 5 being the farthest. )
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.parasiteloot_common.desc=Found in colony mega-structures. Hurts the player when taking items. Damage is increased when the container is more empty (refer to progress bar).
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.infestation_purifier.desc=A creative-only block that removes beckon infestations when using a diamond. It is required that there be no nearby beckons.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.parasitemouth.desc=A fleshy parasite mouth embedded in the ground. Anything that steps directly on it gets bitten, taking armor-piercing damage and gaining corrosive and viral infections. Parasites and players in Creative mode are unaffected.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.relay_base.desc=Used in the Relay tower construction. Placed on the bottom.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.relay_middle.desc=Used in the Relay tower construction. Placed in the middle.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.relay_roof.desc=Used in the Relay tower construction. Placed on the top.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.biomepurifier.desc=Purifies the beckon Infestation if left alone and there are no Beckons nearby. Interacting with Purifier removes parasite biomes LOGICALLY once node has been cleared.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.infested_remain.desc=Can be removed using fire. Used in crafting and harvesting of Residue Bloomings.
bestiary.block.subspaceparasite.diseased_sponge.desc=Can be brewed with water bottles or Awkward Potions to create §2Dead Blood Fluid§7.


