# Bestiary Potion descriptions
bestiary.effect.dod_smoke_trail.desc=A constant trail of thick smoke follows the afflicted entity.
bestiary.effect.bleed.desc=The host suffers continuous internal bleeding. Damage scales with maximum health and worsens while moving.
bestiary.effect.conta.desc=The host is biologically contaminated, suffering periodic damage and risking spread to nearby entities.
bestiary.effect.corrosive.desc=Corrosive substances eat away at the host, dealing periodic damage over time.
bestiary.effect.foster.desc=The host is marked as suitable for parasitic growth, drawing the attention and protection of nearby parasites.
bestiary.effect.prey.desc=The host is designated as prey, making them more likely to be hunted and targeted by parasites.
bestiary.effect.needler.desc=Parasitic growths erupt from the host, launching needle-like projectiles that damage nearby entities.
bestiary.effect.overheating.desc=The host's body overheats, suffering escalating damage as internal systems begin to fail.
bestiary.effect.spotted.desc=The host has been marked and is easier for parasites to track and locate.
bestiary.effect.the_sign.desc=The host bears a mark of significance. Parasites will ignore their presence while the sign persists. The Sign is a bright red symbol possessed by only a select number of people. Among these individuals, the Sign is considered to be a signifier of traits such as great potential, specialness, and competent leadership. The Sign grants immunity to Derived Distortion Phenomenon and parasite aggression.
bestiary.effect.thornshade_thorns.desc=Barbed growths erupt from the host, damaging those who physically strike them. The host will violently erupt if afflicted with said-affect more than 2 times. Nearby entities afflicted with same affects and will erupt if too close to the host during eruption. Does not break tiles.
bestiary.effect.coth.desc=An assimilative infection that escalates in stages. It can refresh and intensify, spread to nearby living hosts (unless repelled), and eventually trigger conversion when the host is weakened or progression thresholds are met.
bestiary.effect.viral.desc=A rapidly mutating infection spreads through the host, dealing periodic damage and risking transmission to nearby living entities. Higher effect levels increase severity and spread potential.
bestiary.effect.jugg.desc=A dislodgement-bound effect that triggers on death. Depending on active Dislo codes, nearby parasites may be healed, nearby non-parasites may be damaged, and nearby players may suffer exhaustion. Certain deaths also apply a Jugg surge to the killer for a short time, with strength tied to stored dislocation values.
bestiary.effect.senses.desc=The host's sensory perception is heightened, increasing detection and follow range.
bestiary.effect.repel.desc=A repellent mark that protects the host from Call of the Hive infection. While active, it can block assimilation-related behaviors such as conversion/transform triggers and helps prevent nearby spread.
bestiary.effect.rage.desc=The host enters a violent frenzy, increasing movement speed and attack damage. Both bonuses can be multiplied and scale with effect strength (values are configuration-based).
bestiary.effect.primitive.desc=Damage dealt to primitive parasite variants is reduced while this effect is active.
bestiary.effect.adapted.desc=Damage dealt to adapted parasite variants is reduced while this effect is active.
bestiary.effect.pure.desc=Damage dealt to pure parasite variants is reduced while this effect is active.
bestiary.effect.crude.desc=Damage dealt to crude parasite variants is reduced while this effect is active.
bestiary.effect.feral.desc=Damage dealt to feral parasite variants is reduced while this effect is active.
bestiary.effect.nexus.desc=Damage dealt to nexus-linked parasite entities is reduced while this effect is active.
bestiary.effect.pivot.desc=While active, kills contribute increased evolution/progression points (scaled by a multiplier and effect strength), and certain parasite events may treat pivot-marked entities as a stronger "signal" when evaluating spawns or stages.
bestiary.effect.parate.desc=A mutative surge that boosts core combat stats. While active, the host's maximum health, armor, and attack damage are increased by a percentage of their base values (scaled by effect strength and configuration multiplier).
bestiary.effect.novision.desc=The host's vision is smothered by a full-screen impairment and mining fatigue is applied; commonly inflicted while a parasite is latched onto host.
bestiary.effect.muscleout.desc=Greatly increases the host's outgoing damage. Attacks are multiplied by a configuration-based factor that scales with effect strength (amplifier + 1).
bestiary.effect.link.desc=Links the host to a colony network. While active, colony-related reactions (such as adaptation/colony triggers) become more likely, scaling with effect strength. Some colony entities can also propagate Link to nearby parasites, synchronizing them as part of the colony.
bestiary.effect.fear.desc=A crippling panic response that disrupts control. At higher levels it can randomly prevent using items or interacting with blocks, cancelling item use outright (subject to blacklist/whitelist rules). Fear also amplifies fall damage and can increase damage taken while airborne, scaling with effect strength and configuration.
bestiary.effect.indeaf.desc=Severs movement control. While active, movement inputs (forward/back/jump) are forcibly disabled and horizontal motion is continually cancelled, effectively rooting the host in place.
bestiary.effect.effectpos.desc=Punishes beneficial effects. The host suffers damage based on the number of active positive potion effects, scaling with effect strength.
bestiary.effect.effectneg.desc=Intensifies harmful effects. While active, negative potion effects on the host are strengthened, scaling with effect strength.
bestiary.effect.debar.desc=Suppresses parasite loot. Parasites affected by Debar will not generate their configured drops on death (respecting the doMobLoot gamerule).
bestiary.effect.braining.desc=Disrupts perception of parasites. While active, parasite entities will not render on the client (they still exist and act normally), updated once per-second.
bestiary.effect.antimall.desc=Reduces or removes adaptive resistance in malleable parasites.

# Bestiary Systems

bestiary.tab.systems=Systems
bestiary.systems.title=Systems
bestiary.systems.home=Home
bestiary.systems.id=ID
bestiary.systems.none=No systems found.
bestiary.systems.missing_desc=Missing description.

bestiary.system.reinforcement.name=Reinforcements
bestiary.system.reinforcement.desc=When a parasite is killed, it may signal for help. A Beckon can appear nearby and begin summoning allies. Beckons grow through stages, and higher stages bring stronger or more numerous reinforcements, allowing small encounters to escalate rapidly. It is paramount that Beckons are removed before they're able to grow and evolve.

bestiary.system.merge.name=Merge
bestiary.system.merge.desc=Assimilated creatures can fuse and reform into new entities. Depending on conditions, merged forms may be selected from specific outcomes or generated randomly.

bestiary.system.status_effects.name=Status Effects
bestiary.system.status_effects.desc=The parasite inflicts unique status effects such as Fear, COTH, Needler, Bleeding, and Camouflage. These effects interfere with combat, movement, and survival, often stacking or intensifying the longer an encounter continues. Be very cautious when these effects are active.

bestiary.system.evolution.name=Evolution
bestiary.system.evolution.desc=The infection progresses through evolution phases as it gains strength. Each phase unlocks more behaviors and mechanics. Certain actions, such as using Lure Blocks, can reduce evolution and slow the outbreak's growth.

bestiary.system.hives.name=Hives
bestiary.system.hives.desc=Hives are structures that organize and defend parasite territory.

bestiary.system.collective_consciousness.name=Collective Consciousness
bestiary.system.collective_consciousness.desc=Parasites can act as a single coordinated organism. With Collective Consciousness active, nearby entities share awareness and respond together.

bestiary.system.eiv.name=Vectors
bestiary.system.eiv.desc=When Emerging Infestation Vectors are enabled, parasites can only spawn naturally within the area of an active Vector. These zones can grow over time, and parasites cannot naturally spawn outside of them. If that restriction is disabled in config or SP world options, parasites are no longer confined to Vector zones and may spawn naturally throughout the world. Each Vector has health points that increase whenever a parasite kills a mob or assimilates one. When either of those happens, the total health of that mob is added to the Vector’s own health. The radius and health of Vectors can also increase independently each day, or roughly every 24000 ticks. To view a Vector's information, place a Vector Module into an Array and press 'Scan'.
bestiary.system.scent.name=Scent
bestiary.system.scent.desc=The parasite reacts to activity through 'scent' buildup. As scent levels rise, waves of enemies become more frequent and more aggressive. Careless combat or lingering in infested areas can draw increasingly dangerous responses.
subspaceparasite.msg.scent.closest_notified=Closest Scent was notified
subspaceparasite.msg.scent.deployed_area=A Scent has been deployed in this area
subspaceparasite.msg.scent.active=Scent is active

bestiary.system.ubiquitous_development.name=Ubiquitous Development
bestiary.system.ubiquitous_development.desc=As parasites grow further, new systems begin to activate across the world. Higher development levels unlock mechanics such as coordinated behavior, merging, scent waves, structures, and expanded spawning rules.

bestiary.system.dislodgment.name=Dislodgment
bestiary.system.dislodgment.desc=Certain actions can disturb the infection and provoke retaliation. Dislodgment triggers can activate through interaction, recovery, or parasite activity, escalating responses through multiple tiers of strength. To view the current dislodgment codes and their effects, place a Dislodgment Module in the array and press scan.

bestiary.system.generations.name=Generations
bestiary.system.generations.desc=Incremental difficulty and tweaks to parasite stats and relating systems. Parasites matures through said-generations over time. Each generation requires sustained growth, and mismatched conditions can slow progress.

bestiary.system.vectors.name=Vectors
bestiary.system.vectors.desc=Emerging Infestation Vectors are areas where most parasites are allowed to spawn naturally. If vector spawning is enabled, natural parasite spawns are usually limited to the range of an active Vector. Active Vectors can be viewed with the Vector Module. Every 24000 ticks, the first Vector has a 1 in 3 chance to appear. Once at least one Vector exists, additional Vector creation checks have a 1 in 10 chance to succeed.

bestiary.system.colonies.name=Colonies
bestiary.system.colonies.desc=Colonies are established 'industrial' segments of the infection. They strengthen parasite presence in an area and make infestations harder to remove. Sponges can be used to remove Dead Blood from Colony structures.

bestiary.system.nodes.name=Nodes
bestiary.system.nodes.desc=Nodes serve as infrastructure for parasite expansion. When active, they support spreading and reinforce nearby growth.

bestiary.system.nests.name=Nests
bestiary.system.nests.desc=Specialized Relay(Nexus) parasites such as Dispatchers can form nests that accelerate growth and expansion for the hive. These sites rapidly turn surrounding terrain into active and foggy infestation zones. A Fog Nullifier can be used to remove said-fog.

bestiary.system.variants.name=Variants
bestiary.system.variants.desc=Parasites have a chance to spawn from an array of variants that are not limited to inflicting viral, bleeding, or doing more damage to blocks.

bestiary.system.derived_distortion.name=Derived Distortion Phenomenon
bestiary.system.derived_distortion.desc=Derived parasites emit a disruptive phenomenon that interferes with nearby analysis tools and interfaces. When one is close enough, affected GUI pages may display scrambled text, falsified readouts, and distorted values instead of reliable information. This proximity-based effect causes a black, oily substance to seep from the victim's eyes, while thoughts and senses take on the feeling of a rough, staticky granite surface.
